Auto Scaling Group (ASG)
What is Auto Scaling Group?

An Auto Scaling Group (ASG) is an AWS service that automatically adds or removes EC2 instances based on application traffic.

Its main goal is to keep your application available while reducing unnecessary costs.

Real-Life Example

Imagine a restaurant.

On weekdays, 2 employees are enough.
On weekends, more customers arrive, so the manager calls 3 more employees.
When customers leave, those extra employees go home.

👉 ASG works the same way with EC2 instances.

Why Do We Use ASG?
Automatically adds EC2 instances when traffic increases.
Automatically removes EC2 instances when traffic decreases.
Keeps the application running if an EC2 instance fails.
Saves money by running only the required number of servers.
