ASG Settings
Minimum Capacity

The minimum number of EC2 instances that should always be running.

Example: 2

Desired Capacity

The number of EC2 instances you want running under normal conditions.

Example: 3

Maximum Capacity

The maximum number of EC2 instances ASG can launch.

Example: 10

Interview Question

Q: What is an Auto Scaling Group?

Answer:
An Auto Scaling Group (ASG) is an AWS service that automatically increases or decreases the number of EC2 instances based on application demand, ensuring high availability and cost optimization.

Easy Way to Remember

ASG = Automatic EC2 Manager

Just like a restaurant manager adds more staff when customers increase and sends them home when business is slow, ASG automatically adds or removes EC2 instances based on traffic.

Interview Tip

Remember this simple relationship:

Launch Template
       │
       ▼
Auto Scaling Group (ASG)
       │
       ▼
Elastic Load Balancer (ELB)
Launch Template → Defines how to create an EC2 instance.
ASG → Decides how many EC2 instances should run.
ELB → Distributes traffic among those EC2 instances.

This is a very common interview question for AWS and DevOps roles.
